
Louis shifted his weight, trying to get comfortable next to Harry even though the dorm mattress protested under their combined weight . It was barely a decent bed for one person, much less two.
"We shouldn't be doing this," Louis murmured against Harry's pale skin, tracing his fingers against the curves of the younger boy's tattoos.
"You, you don't want to?" Harry asked, his green eyes heavy lidded and dark, his brows drawing together in confusion.
"I never said I didn't want to," Louis whispered, tugging Harry's shirt down a little so he could press his lips against Harry's collarbones, his lips soft against Harry's swallow tattoos. "I just said we shouldn't."